title: 820-00165 Green Light No Fan
message:
Hi all, have a 00165 on the bench that's being stubborn. Has green/amber light but no fan spin, 20mA from the power supply. Originally had some corrosion around U8130 and J6100 and the DC board and flex were destroyed, replaced the board and flex and cleaned the corrosion, got green light back but same power draw.

PPBUS_G3H 8.62v
PP3V42_G3H 3.42v
PPVRTC_G3H 3.34v
PP5V_S5 5.01v
PP3V3_S5 3.35v

PM_BATLOW_L 3.3v
SMC_ADAPTER_EN 3.43v
PM_DSW_PWRGD 3.43v
PCH_DSWVRMEN 3.23v 

[B]PP3V3_SUS 0v
P3V3SUS_EN 0v[/B]

RTC_RESET_L 3.34v
PCH_SRTCRST_L 3.34v
PCH_INTRUDER_L 3.05v
PCH_INTVRMEN 3.25v

Any suggestions? Been reading some other threads and it seems like it may be PCH related.

title: 820-00165 Green Light No Fan
message:
Heat PCH area with quality flux.
Possibly accumulated crap...
